parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Loss and Erratic Idle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause the vehicle to limp or stall, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on highways. Erratic idle can lead to reduced engine performance and decreased fuel efficiency.
symptoms: Check Engine Light (CEL) and other warning lights on the driver's information display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation or delay in the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to roll backward on inclines, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: Hesitation or delay between the electric engine stopping and the gas engine re-engaging

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Engine Racing in Hybrid Vehicles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended racing of the engine can cause the vehicle to lurch forward, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions, especially when stopped at intersections.
symptoms: the vehicle feels like it might lurch forward from a stop
the problem usually occurs within the first 5 minutes of driving and first 3-5 miles of driving.
